You are the most universal mythical beast ever. Sightings of the unicorn have been reported from all over the world, even in modern times. Unicorns are pure and incorruptible. In China, unicorns symbolized gentleness, good will, and wisdom. Christianity links the unicorn with Christ. It is said that unicorns would only allow virgin girls to see them, let alone touch them. They were easily lured into fatal ambushes by a virgin with some poachers waiting for the unicorn in nearby bushes. A unicorn's horn was a highly prized possession, which was reputed to have great healing capabilities. With the touch of its horn, a unicorn could bring back a person who had been dead for several hours. But when separated from the unicorn's body, the magic was significantly reduced. The unicorn had the body of a horse, a unique spiraling horn, and a lion's tail. They were pure white in color.
What mythical beast best represents you? Take the quiz!"

event,"Hello to all my dear friends!  I miss all of you.  Well the only thing I hae to say for now, is what had went on last night and today.  Well last night I slept over at my cousin Meli's house, and we talked just about the whole night.  We got on the computer where she introduced me to one of her friends, and now we friends.  He is a really awesome guy.  Well after I met him, Meli and I went and played on the Quiji board.  We didn't play long though.  Finally about three O'clock in the morning we decided to go to bed.  We woke up at about nine O'clock in the morning and decided to be lazy all day, because we both weren't feeling well.  At about five O'clock I had to come back home, although I really didn't want to leave Meli, who is sick with a sore throat.  When I got home I helped my little eleven year old brother cook dinner, which was sloppy joe.  After I ate dinner I went to my room to watch television, and put a 500 piece puzzle together.  (I'm nowhere near finished it.)  Then after a while I decided to make some beignets (pronounced ""Ben-Yay"").  Which came out really good.  After that I decided to get on the computer to check my mail and to chat.  Which only two people happened to come on-line, and that was Meli and my new friend Xela.  Well that is all I have to say for now.  I love you all and good nighty night.  *kisses and hugs everyone*  Bye."

Sorry everyone, it has been over a month that I have been able to get on-line. Well I have graduated high school, May 19th. Today is my last day at my job which I have worked here for school. I have started a new job last weekend, at a child care, a very stressful job. I'm going to start college in fall for my basic courses, then I will continue at a different college to one day become a Funeral Director. Right now I'm at work, and I'm so bored, they told me since today is my last day, to just take a break.  One of my co-workers gave me her password so I can get on the internet, so I won't be so bored.  My co-workers, and my boss had set up a ""lunch meeting"" today, so I ordered my lunch the other day.  I go to the lunch meeting today, eat my lunch, after that, everyone was really quite, one of my co-workers said she'll be right back, she comes in with a cake, for the ""lunch meeting"" and come to find out it was a ""Graduation cake"" for this girl Nikki and me.  Then they gave us a graduation card, with everyone's singniture, and $52.50 in the card.  The cake was half blue and yellow, which is Nikki's school colors, and half maroon and white, which is my school colors.  It was pretty cool, but I didn't really enjoy being in a room full of people, when I was eating, then when they are sitting there looking at us when we are opening our card and stuff.  I was thinking the whole time, ""Oh gosh, Please Help Me!!!""  Well I must be going now.  I hope to continue to get on the computer often. Bye and take care."

Well today is my birthday.  I make 18.  Thank goodness.  I was supposed to go out tonight, but I'm not feeling well.  I have a sinus cold, and I'm taking medicine, which doesn't seem to be helping me any.  Work has been hectic for me, because we have this thing called ""The March Turnaround"", which makes us have plenty of work.  Ok I could have sworn someone just walked in my room, but there is no one in there.  Probably some spirit, they love to play in my room.  They get aggrevating sometimes.  Especially when they have this dude that watches me sleep, he makes me feel uncomfortable.  Well I must go for now.  I have to go to bed, I have school and work in the morning.  Well goodnight and hope to be back on here sometime this weekend."

event,"Hello to all my friends and family!!!

Sorry I haven't been on in a while.  Mardi Gras holidays were February 23-25, I didn't get to go to any parades, although I truely wanted to.  So, instead I did something better, which was paint my room.  I've been wanting my room painted in sun, moon, and stars theme for over a year, and now it is finally being done.  I'm still not done, but I'm getting there.  Just with school and work in the way it's hard to do what I want to do.
Well I hope everyone is doing good.  Take care, my dear beloved friends.

Your soul is bound to the Solitary Rose: The
Alone.

""When I wake up alone, the shades are still
drawn on the cold window pane so they cast
their lines on my bed and lines on my
face.""

The Solitary Rose is associated with loneliness,
melancholy, and patience. It is governed by
the goddess Merope and its sign is The Sword,
or Unrequited Love.

As a Solitary Rose, you may be summed up as a
hopeless romantic. You desire love and have so
much love to give, but thing just never seem to
work out the way you want them to. In life,
you can be very optomistic, even when things
are gray and nothing works out to your
expectations.
